      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, there are definitely ways to speed things up and stop that interest monster from gobbling up all your payments! The most direct way is to make extra payments, which is essentially throwing extra gold at the principal balance. If you can throw an extra payment at the loan, it goes straight to reducing the base amount the interest is calculated on next month.\n\nAnother tactic, if your loan allows it, is to explore refinancing. This means taking out a new loan with a lower interest rate, which immediately lowers that monthly interest calculation. It's like finding a secret, less-guarded path through the goblin tunnels—a lower rate means less tribute to the interest beast! Even just making one extra payment a quarter, instead of waiting for the full monthly cycle, can make a noticeable difference.",
